author: @DickyBenfield
text: I never noticed anything on that video that implied there was some members only thing... and maybe I am misunderstanding what people were worked up about? But frankly, even if you decided to do a bunch of members only stuff, that is your choice to make... I'm not gonna judge you for what you do. I can't imagine growing a business where the income was based only on something as fickle as YouTube's monetization. I admire that you do as much as you do freely. But if someone says to me, "Hey, I'm going to give you some free stuff" I'm NOT going to say "Now you HAVE to give me everything for free, even if it costs you and you may not be able to recover those costs, I don't care!!! Free for me or NOT AT ALL!!!" That just seems absurd... I will continue to be subscribed and watch your videos as long as the content is entertaining and/or teaches me about things I want to know, regardless of other content you may or may not produce for "members". Thanks for all of the great videos, I've learned a lot and enjoyed them!
